feedback_history.text:
-= Kitchen =-
You've just walked into a kitchen. Let's see what's in here.

You can see a fridge. You see an oven. Huh, weird. You see a table. The table is massive. Unfortunately, there isn't a thing on it. You can see a counter. The counter is vast. On the counter you make out a cookbook. Suddenly, you bump your head on the ceiling, but it's not such a bad bump that it's going to prevent you from looking at objects and even things. If you haven't noticed it already, there seems to be something there by the wall, it's a stove. But the thing hasn't got anything on it. You make a mental note to not get your hopes up the next time you see a stove in a room.

There is an open patio door leading north. There is a closed plain door leading west. There is an exit to the east. Don't worry, there is no door.
